Q. Maximum number of visible points


Circular structure breaks this property:

“There is a clear start → end ordering.”
We don’t always need to linearize circular data.
But to use linear techniques like sliding window or binary search, we have to.
Think of it as - straightening a circle in a linear line from point 0 to 360.

Circular structure can bring overlap. Which is the biggest problem.


🔵 Pattern 1: Duplicate (Unroll the circle)
❓ “Do I need a continuous window?”
Use when:

* range/window problems
* need ordering

for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    arr.add(arr.get(i) + offset); // or just arr[i]
}

✔️ Used in:

* angle problems
* circular subarray windows

